  "prompt": "What is the impact of Facebook on India's economy and its future growth?",
  "response": "Facebook (now Meta) has had several significant impacts on India's economy and potential future growth:\n\n1. Digital Connectivity\n- Increased internet access and digital connectivity\n- Enabled small businesses to reach wider markets\n- Provided platforms for digital entrepreneurship\n- Connected rural and urban populations\n\n2. Economic Opportunities\n- Created jobs in digital marketing and social media\n- Supported digital advertising ecosystem\n- Facilitated e-commerce growth\n- Platform for startup ecosystem\n\n3. Technology Investment\n- Significant investments in Indian tech infrastructure\n- Supported digital transformation initiatives\n- Developed local talent and technology capabilities\n- Partnerships with Indian tech companies\n\n4. Financial Inclusion\n- WhatsApp payments integration\n- Digital financial services\n- Easier access to financial tools for underserved populations\n\n5. Challenges\n- Data privacy concerns\n- Potential market manipulation\n- Digital divide issues\n- Regulatory challenges\n\n6. Future Potential\n- Expanding digital infrastructure\n- Supporting digital skill development\n- Potential for artificial intelligence and emerging technologies\n- Continued platform innovation\n\nOverall, Facebook has been a significant catalyst for digital economic growth in India, with both positive contributions and potential challenges.",
